title: Top 25 Volleyball Rankings
text:
Joshua J. Grine NMPreps.com Editor 
Each week on NMPreps.com we update our New Mexico High School Volleyball Rankings. Here is our latest Top 10 rankings, to access our Top 25 please become a premium subscriber. Top 25 Rankings Here - Subscriber Feature 
Pictured is the La Cueva Lady Bears who are No. 1 with a 15-0, 5-0 record on the season 
(Overall Record, District Record) 
1. La Cueva (15-0, 5-0): Went 1-0 this week. Beat No. 11 Eldorado. 2. St. Pius X (14-2, 3-0): Went 3-0 this week. Beat No. 16 Academy, No. 17 Moriary, & Santa Fe. 3. Sandia Prep (17-0, 5-0): Went 2-0 this week. Beat Hope Christian & Santa Fe Indian. 4. Centennial (14-2, 5-1): Went 2-0. Beat No. 8 Los Lunas & No. 19 Santa Teresa. 5. Onate (11-5, 4-0): Went 1-0. Beat No. 13 Mayfield. 6. Texico (13-1, 2-0): Went 3-0. Beat Portales, Eunice & Dexter. Moved +2 7. Volcano Vista (10-5, 4-1): Went 0-1. Lost to No. 11 Cibola. Moved -1 8. Los Lunas (11-4, 5- ): Went 1-1. Beat Valencia. Lost to Centennial. Moved -1 9. Roswell (14-2, 2-0): Went 2-0. Beat Artesia & Lovington. 10. Cleveland (8-8, 3-1): Went 1-0. Beat Rio Rancho. 
Notes: 3A Texico moved up again to No. 6, highest ranking for a small school division (3A-1A) team. Artesia back into the rankings after falling out last week. Gadsden moves into the rankings and leap frogs to 22 with win over Las Cruces. Mayfield had the biggest drop from 13 to 18 with an 0-2 week. West Las Vegas the +2 movement, 12 game winning streak moves them to 14-1 on the season. 
What else is to come in Week 10 Playoff Predictions.
